node.text: @highsnobietydesign: @lego adds the fan-favorite The Child and The Mandalorian to its BrickHeadz line-up. The Child will come in its hoverpram while The Mandalorian comes equipped with its signature weapons. Pre-orders are open now and release is set for August 1st. #hsdesign

@calaiscampbell is this edition’s Off-Field MVP. Campbell, a defensive end for the Jacksonville Jaguars, was named this year’s NFL Walter Payton Man of the Year for his contributions in the local Jacksonville community with the @crcfoundation, a group he started in honor of his late father.

@highsnobietydesign: @hotwheelsofficial turned @teslamotors’ Cybertruck into a limited edition 1:10 scale remote control car. 🏎

The R/C is now available for pre-order via Hot Wheels’ website for $400 USD, and is expected to ship in December. A smaller, 1:64 scale version will also be available for $20 USD.

During the @nba's 2020 All-Star Weekend in Chicago, we paid a visit to Mountain Dew's Courtside Studios to catch up with @zionwilliamson, @chicagodonc and @scottiepippen. Stay tuned to our Instagram page for tomorrow's premiere of their #CopOrDrop episode.

@highsnobietydesign: @banksy’s Valentine’s Day mural in Bristol’s Barton Hill was recently vandalized, but he’s not too bothered. In fact, he’s “glad” it was vandalized as he preferred his initial sketches over the final piece.

While the @adidasoriginals Superstar has since traded in its basketball glory for a more casual pedigree, it’s become the go-to shoe for a new generation of creators who value style just as much as the next NBA star. So what better way to show them off than to layer up and stunt in the city that helped elevate basketball to new heights? We connected with local creatives from Chicago who styled the iconic shell toes their own way.

@highsnobietystyle: @craig__green ’s latest Genius collection for @moncler includes jackets that resemble down quilts—long, formless and flowing—with the silhouette of the body printed on the outside of them. 👤⠀

@highsnobietyshop: Those who have seen the @colette_mon_amour documentary will know that @virgilabloh — founder of @off____white, was a big fan of the store. Virgil Abloh is featured in the documentary and we are excited to say that we have collaborated with @off____white for this celebratory collection.⁠

Skijoring was first introduced during the 1928 Winter Olympics when skiers were pulled across the race track at maximum speed by riderless horses. The sport later permitted the skiers to be pulled by cars in 1953.

We ventured to Austria's Zell am See, to witness the sport in action during the 2020 @gpicerace. During the winter of 2019 the ice race motorsport returned to Zell am See for the first time after around 45 years.
